<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,942,1331]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1050,1076]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The forewing length is 
<quantity box="[589,654,1051,1077]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
in the 
<typeStatus box="[731,829,1051,1077]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">holotype</typeStatus>
male. 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[904,1154,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Hampsonascia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aulaca" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[904,1154,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">Hampsonascia aulaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1161,1224,1051,1077]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1161,1224,1051,1077]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is externally reminiscent of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1894" box="[269,426,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Miltochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentifascia">
<emphasis box="[269,426,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">H. dentifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[481,626,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Hampsonascia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thaifascia" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[481,626,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">H. thaifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[634,697,1087,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[634,697,1087,1113]" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
but can be distinguished in the smaller size, the presence of three subbasal spots and the shorter and broader zigzags of the postmedial line. The male genitalia of the new species are clearly different from those of other congeners by the broader vesica bearing four clusters of large spines and having an unilobate distal diverticulum, a feature unique within the genus. The detailed comparison with 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2021" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2021" box="[1257,1395,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Hampsonascia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saldaitisi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1257,1395,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">H. saldaitisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="95">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="13" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is provided above in the diagnosis of the latter species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
